Americans began donning face masks this week after federal and local officials changed their position on whether face coverings protect against coronavirus.
But not for Muslim women who wear the niqab, or Islamic face veil.
Research confirms that Muslim women who wear Islamic dress in non-Muslim majority countries are frequently subjected to abuse.
In a 2017 American study of 40 Muslim women, 85% reported verbal violence and 25% had experienced physical violence.
For now, niqab-wearing women say, they are in high demand as experts on face covering.